```

In this program, the `fibonacci` function takes an integer `n` as input and returns the nth number in the sequence. The base cases are when `n` is 0 or 1, in which case the function returns 0 or 1 respectively. For any other value of `n`, the function recursively calls itself with `n-1`, `n-2`, and `n-3` as arguments, and returns the sum of these three results.

